XPath Search plugin for vim.

When editing a valid XML file, you can press SHIFT+X to enter XPath search mode.
A new results window will pop up beneath the current window, with results matching your XPath appearing as you type.
Hitting enter jumps to the results window, and then hitting enter on one of the results jumps to the line in your XML file that matched.

Requires:
-Vim with python support

To install:
-Place all files into your vimXX or .vim directory


